Hungarian Stocks Advance for Second Day, Led by OTP Bank, Mol

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-04-20T07:45:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/hungarian-stocks-advance-for-second-day-led-by-otp-bank-mol.html
Hungary’s benchmark BUX index rose
for a second day, led by OTP Bank Nyrt., the country’s biggest
lender, and Mol Nyrt., the largest oil company.  The BUX index of 13 companies advanced 1.5 percent to
23,963.13 as of 9:30 a.m. in Budapest, extending yesterday’s
1.4 percent rally.  OTP jumped 1.8 percent to 6,190 forint and Mol rose 2.5
percent to 24,500 forint. The two companies together make up 62
percent of the BUX by weighting.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  